The paper deals with knowledge engineering problems for hypothesis generation using AI planning, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of planning for dealing with uncertainty and incomplete model description, which is a common problem in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper proposes a language and a web-based tool for capturing the model description, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the application of hypothesis generation in malware detection, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper proposes a 9-step process for guiding domain experts in specifying the LTS++ model, which falls under the category of social and information sciences (cs.SI).
